om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Robinhood: options</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/24658730.251860/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vc=
GluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDgtMDQvdGhlLXNlYy1oYXMtaXRzLWV5ZS1vbi1jcnlwdG8/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBbc0ca99d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; =
background-color: #ccc;"> talked yesterday</a> about the wild rally in Robi=
nhood Markets Inc. stock, which was up 24% on Tuesday and then up another 5=
0% yesterday. It closed yesterday at $70.39, well above the $38 price in it=
s initial public offering a week ago. My analysis of the situation was basi=
cally to shrug and say =E2=80=9Cmeme stocks, man,=E2=80=9D but I did point =
to a couple of factors =E2=80=94 buying the dip, diamond hands =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0that are often important to meme-stock rallies.</p><p style=3D"margin: 1=
6px 0;">I missed a really important one, though, which is the frantic buyin=
g of=C2=A0short-dated out-of-the-money call options. This has been a long-r=
unning theme in meme stocks: Retail traders will buy call options on a meme=
 stock gambling that it will go up a lot quickly. Options market makers wil=
l hedge the call options they sell by buying the stock, which will make it =
go up. As it goes up, the options will get more in-the-money, which require=
s the market makers to buy more stock to adjust their hedge, which makes it=
 go up more.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When I lay it out like that it=
 sounds like free money, an automatic machine to make stocks go up, and ple=
nty of people on Reddit=C2=A0<em>do=C2=A0</em>lay it out like that and argu=
e that it=E2=80=99s free money and a way to make stocks go up automatically=
. If you had asked me about this last year, I would have said, no, you are =
misunderstanding, you are exaggerating, the world doesn=E2=80=99t work that=
 way. (In fact I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2=
4658730.251860/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIw=
