idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;">asked on Reddit on Tuesday</a>, and =E2=80=A6=C2=A0sort =
of not?</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When Robinhood filed its prospectus=
 for this IPO last month, we talked a bit about its business. What is that =
business? Well, it=E2=80=99s the business of getting people to trade a lot =
of stock options. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
24658730.251860/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzI=
wMjEtMDctMDIvcm9iaW5ob29kLWlwby1maWxpbmctaXMtYS1sZXNzb24taW4tbWVtZS1maW5hbm=
Nl/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb6629082" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border=
-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: soli=
d; background-color: #ccc;"> I wrote</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">It is tempting to joke that Robinhood is a Dogecoin brokerage, b=
ut it isn=E2=80=99t. Economically, Robinhood is an options brokerage. Robin=
hood=E2=80=99s main business is convincing people to trade options, and the=
n having options market makers pay to take the other side of those trades. =
In the first quarter, $197.9 million of Robinhood=E2=80=99s revenue came fr=
om payment for options order flow, representing 38% of its total revenue; s=
tocks and crypto were 26% and 17% respectively. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">If your model is that Robinhood is the brokerage of fun inve=
sting, then options offer even more fun than stocks, so it makes sense that=
 they=E2=80=99re Robinhood=E2=80=99s most lucrative business.</p></blockquo=
te><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When Robinhood went public last week and al=
located 25% of the IPO shares to its retail customers, and then the stock d=
ropped, that seemed, you know, bad for business. Customers want to use Robi=
nhood to buy stocks that go up, and if they all buy Robinhood stock and it =
goes down then they will be disappointed and spend less time on the app and=
 make less money for Robinhood.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But none of=
 that is very important, because=C2=A0<em>really=C2=A0</em>what Robinhood c=
ustomers want is to use Robinhood to buy <em>options </em>that go up, and t=
hat=E2=80=99s really what Robinhood wants them to do, because that=E2=80=99=
s how it really makes=C2=A0money. The fact that Robinhood customers got to =
start buying options this week, and it worked well, is good for Robinhood=
=E2=80=99s <em>business</em>. It is good and salient advertising for the pr=
oduct that makes Robinhood the most money.=C2=A0The possibility that buying=
 short-term out-of-the-money call options on a meme stock is a good way to =
make that stock go up and make your options pay off is =E2=80=A6=C2=A0look,=
 very very very weird =E2=80=A6=C2=A0but also good news=C2=A0for Robinhood.=
 You might even expect it to increase the present value of Robinhood=E2=80=
=99s future cash flows. Maybe that=E2=80=99s why the stock went up.</p><tab=
